  "title": "Market Analyst (Marine)",
  "description": "<p><strong>LOCATED IN THE WEST </strong><br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong><br />• Conduct market research on the maritime and green marine technology sectors, tracking trends of energy-efficient marine solutions.<a href=\"https://www.seaforrest.com/about-us/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a><br />• Collect, analyse, and summarise data on competitors, industry developments, and customer needs to support business strategy.<br />• Prepare reports, dashboards, and presentations to communicate insights on market dynamics and emerging opportunities.<br />• Monitor industry publications, regulatory changes, and sustainability trends that impact the maritime decarbonisation landscape.<br />• Support forecasting and benchmarking activities to inform product positioning and go-to-market decisions.<br />• Work closely with cross-functional teams to gather inputs and align market insights with business goals.<br />• Assist in preparing client materials, tender submissions, and internal briefings with relevant market data.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br />• Bachelor’s degree in Business, Economics, Maritime Studies, Data Analytics, or related field.<br />• 1–3 years of experience in market research, consulting, or analytics, preferably within maritime, shipping, energy, or sustainability domains.<br />• Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret quantitative and qualitative data.<br />• Excellent communication and report-writing skills.<br />• Proficiency in Excel and data visualization tools (e.g., PowerPoint, Tableau).<br />• Interest in sustainability and emerging maritime technologies.</p><p><strong>Preferred:</strong><br />• Familiarity with maritime industry trends, shipping energy transition strategies, or emission reduction technologies.<br />• Experience with secondary research, competitive intelligence, or business intelligence functions.</p>",
